  "local_port": 36924,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good hobbies and interests to put on a resume?",
  "response": "Including hobbies and interests on a resume can help to give employers a more rounded view of your personality and skills. When choosing which hobbies and interests to include, focus on those that are relevant to the job, demonstrate desirable skills, or showcase your character. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **Volunteering**: This shows a commitment to helping others and a strong sense of social responsibility. It can also indicate skills in leadership, teamwork, and organization.\n\n2. **Sports or Fitness Activities**: These can demonstrate discipline, teamwork, and a commitment to health and well-being. For example, running marathons or playing on a sports team.\n\n3. **Creative Pursuits**: Hobbies such as painting, writing, photography, or playing a musical instrument can indicate creativity, patience, and attention to detail.\n\n4. **Technology and Coding**: If you're interested in technology, mention any coding projects or tech-related hobbies. This is particularly relevant for jobs in the tech industry and can show problem-solving skills and a passion for innovation.\n\n5. **Reading**: This can indicate a commitment to lifelong learning and intellectual curiosity. Mentioning specific genres or authors can also provide insight into your personality.\n\n6. **Travel**: Traveling can show that you are adaptable, open-minded, and have a good understanding of different cultures. This is particularly relevant for jobs that involve working with diverse teams or clients.\n\n7. **Outdoor Activities**: Hobbies such as hiking, camping, or gardening can show that you value an active lifestyle and have a connection to nature.\n\n8. **Chess or Strategic Games**: These can indicate strong strategic thinking and problem-solving skills.\n\n9. **Cooking or Baking**: These hobbies can demonstrate creativity, attention to detail, and the ability to follow complex instructions.\n\n10. **Public Speaking or Debate**: These activities can show strong communication skills, confidence, and the ability to think on your feet.\n\nWhen listing hobbies and interests on your resume, keep it concise and relevant. Tailor your choices to the job you're applying for, and make sure they add value to your application.",
